sense.definition: moving or extending so as to end within (something) (e.g., ran into the house)
indicating the clothing being used to dress someone/something (e.g., got into his suit)
indicating a time period (being) entered (e.g., we are into the third week)
to a position of contact with, typically used with verbs expressing forceful motion or collision (e.g., rammed into him)
indicating a topic of observation/analysis (e.g., inquiry into the cause)
expressing a state, condition, form, or activity being entered (e.g., broke into pieces, jolted into despair)
indicating a group/collection (X2) being added or assigned to (as a member) (e.g., election into congress)
taking a lively and active interest with regard to (something) (e.g., got into sky diving)
